Three Chinese linked to the ticketing scandal that has rocked Madaraka Express, and charged with giving a Sh900,000 bribe to influence investigations will stay in police cell longer. A Mombasa court on Friday denied Mr Li Gen, Mr Li Xiaowu and Mr Sun Xin bond and ordered them locked up. Mombasa Chief Magistrate Julius Nangea said the prosecution had given compelling reasons to stop their release. Without demonstrating that the accused have a reasonable fixed abode, the magistrate noted, it would be difficult to guarantee that they will attend court when freed on bond.  More follows.  